red for reduced efficacy of hydrocodone or development of withdrawal symptoms due to reduced plasma hydrocodone levels.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/289050/', '[1] Hutchinson MR, Menelaou A, Foster DJ, Coller JK, Somogyi AA "CYP2D6 and CYP3A4 involvement in the primary oxidative metabolism of hydrocodone by human liver microsomes." Br J Clin Pharmacol 57 (2004):  287-97[2] "Product Information. Zohydro ER (hydrocodone)." Zogenix, Inc  (2013):', 1767363028);
